    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Single-edged knives or short swords used by Saxon and Anglo-Saxon people during the Early Middle Ages. The shape and construction of this weapon varies widely; continental versions have a curved blunt edge while those found in England are straight-backed, with an angled point.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
